If you run a meetup or are aware of a group of people meeting and discussing Emacs, please add them here so other people can connect.

Check out Bhavin Gandhi's EmacsConf 2022 talk on [https://emacsconf.org/2022/talks/meetups/ attending and organizing Emacs meetups].

Meeting other Emacs geeks is a great way to pick up ideas and learn even more.  Can't find an Emacs meetup near you? [http://harryrschwartz.com/2015/09/14/starting-an-emacs-meetup.html Here are a few tips on starting an Emacs meetup].  Have fun!

You can also find a list of upcoming events in the weekly [https://sachachua.com/blog/category/emacs-news Emacs News newsletter] or add this [https://emacslife.com/calendar/emacs-calendar.ics iCalendar file] to your calendar.  [https://emacslife.com/calendar/ The Emacs Calendar] has other options.

